summary:
Focus - Corporate Law, Contracts and Capital Markets. 
Activities:
- Corporate Secretarial Services (drafting Shareholders Resolutions, Board Resolutions, Call Notices and Administration Proposals);
- Drafting internal guidelines in connection with Corporate Governance and Compliance;
- Advice regarding CVM and BACEN regulations, as well as compliance with International Laws;
- Drafting and Reviewing all kinds of Contracts; 
- Coordinating Due Diligence with all Company Departments and
- Participating and assisting corporate reorganization transactions and M&As.
Ability to communicate effectively/cleary and work in an organized manner at dynamic environment with internal clients who need fast answers. Proactive, diligent, committed, discreet, organized, mature and with excellent relation with coworkers.

profile_positions.description:
Responsible for day to day business in the Netherlands, Austria and Singapore;
Responsible for cost reduction in the Netherlands and Austria;
Participating in meeting with Stakeholders, Suppliers and Government;
Compliance with Dutch, Austrian and Asian tax authorities; and
Focal point for continuing the restructuring process implementation.

- Activities
- Corporate Services such as drafting and coordinating Brazilian, Austrian, Dutch and Asian corporate documents and filing before the respective Chamber of Commerce;
- Advice regarding Shareholders Meeting, Board Meeting, Board of Auditors, Committees, as well coordinating the attendance of Shareholders;
- Assisting Investors Relations Department (Advising, Drafting Forms, ITR);
- Compliance with CVM, BM&F Bovespa Regulations and others Administrative Agencies; 
- Handling corporate matters with foreigners investors;
- Compliance with obligations arising from Shareholders Agreement and Company's By-Laws;
- Drafting and Revising Brazilian and International all types of Contracts;
- Drafting Brazilian and International Power of Attorneys;
- Trademark Application;
- Assisting Bidding Process;
- Advising all sort of legal matters in connection with Corporate Law, Tax, International Law, Intectual Property and others;
- Advising/Monitoring day to day activities of International Subsidiaries and its employees;
- Legal Advice to all Company's Internal Departments;
- Drafting and Revising internal rules; 
- Assisting Finance Transactions and Debt Restructure deals;
- Coordinating the full range of corporate national and international transactions, such as capital increase/funding,foreign exchange transactions, leasing, swap and hedge;
- Coordinating due diligences; 
- Coordinating incorporation and dissolution of Companies in Austria, The Netherlands and Singapore; and
- Assisting the Judicial Recovery of the Company.

Part of EBX Corporate Finance team that collaborated with the performance of all transactions involving EBX group of companies in connection with M&As, Finance, Capital Markets and Corporate Matters. 
Activities:
- Coordinating split and reverse split;
- Assisted the issuance of MMX Private Debentures in the total amount of USD 200MM;
- Assisted the Transaction whereby Wuhan Iron and Steel (Group) Co. invested US$400 in MMX; 
- Participated in meetings and assisted the studies for creating EBX BRAZIL GROWTH FUND L.P; 
- Coordinating requests to Securities and Exchange Commission of Brazil - CVM; and
- Assisted Participation Notes Transaction with Banco Itaú Europa S.A.

focus - Corporate Law, Capital Markets and M&As.
Activities:
- Assisted structuring the Stock Option Program;
- Participated in structuring the Global Depositary Receipts Program;
- Assisted MMX IPO in June 2006 that raised a total of US$ 1.4 bn; 
- Assisted the Transaction whereby Cleveland-Cliffs Inc acquired 30% stake of MMX Amapa Iron Project for US$133 MM; 
- Assisted the Long Term Finance with Banco Itaú BBA S.A. and Banco ABC Brasil S.A in respect of MMX Amapa Iron Project in the total amount of US$250 MM.
- Assisted the Transaction whereby Anglo American Plc. acquired 30% Stake in MMX Minas-Rio Iron Project for US$ 2.5 bn; 
- Assisted the listing of MMX Global Depositary Receipts in Toronto Stock Exchange;
- Assisted the Transaction whereby Ontario Teachers’ Pension Plan Board acquired a 15% stake in the logistic project for US$185 MM; 
- Assisted the Long Term Finance for MMX Minas-Rio Iron Project; and
- Assisted the Transaction whereby Anglo American Plc acquired IronX Company for US$ 5.5 bn.

Focus - Litigation
Activities:
- Monitoring Case Records;
- Drafting all types of motions; 
- Assisting attorneys with the documents for preparing court filings;
- Drafting reports contemplating the status of the litigation cases; 
- Monitoring new regulations;
- Researches in respect of law doctrine and Courts jurisprudence; and
- Monitoring external lawyers in different states in Brazil.
